Noncommercial Purpose

Noncommercial purposes include any use that is not a commercial advantage or
private monetary compensation. Noncommercial purposes also include using the
software, modifications, or new works based on the software for your own
internal use, research, education, and personal projects.

The following are not Noncommercial Purposes. They require a separate commercial
license from the licensor:

1.  providing the software as a paid service or product;
2.  using the software to provide a commercial service or in a commercial
    workflow;
3.  redistributing the software as part of a commercial product or offering;
4.  any use primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or
    private monetary compensation.

